        <h1>OCCAM'S RAZOR</h1>
        <span class="meta">ENTRY 002 /// COGNITIVE LOAD</span>

        <p>Walk past any field at the Naperville Park District on a Saturday, and you’ll hear it. The "Joystick Coach."</p>
        <p><em>"Pass left! Step up! Shoot! No, the other way!"</em></p>
        <p>These are well-meaning mentors who believe that more information equals better performance. But <strong>Cognitive Load Theory</strong> tells us the exact opposite.</p>

        <div class="math-box">
            EXECUTION = BANDWIDTH - (COMPLEXITY + NOISE)
        </div>

        <h2>The Bandwidth Equation</h2>
        <p>Every time you shout an instruction from the sideline, you are adding <strong>Noise</strong>. You think you are helping. In reality, you are stealing their bandwidth.</p>

        <h2>The Protocol: Silence</h2>
        <p>Next practice, try an experiment. Play a 10-minute scrimmage with a strict rule: <strong>Zero Talking.</strong> Watch the players stop looking at you for answers and start looking at the field.</p>
